{{Refimprove|date=May 2011}}{{Infobox scientist | name = Barouh V. Berkovits | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Lucenec]], [[Czechoslovakia]] | death_date = {{death date|2012|10|23}} | death_place = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | ethnicity = | field = [[Biomedical Engineering]] | work_institution = [[Medtronic]] | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = | known_for = | author_abbreviation_bot = | author_abbreviation_zoo = | prizes = Distinguished Scientist Award from the Heart Rhythm Society | religion = | footnotes = }} '''Barouh Berkovits''' (May 7, 1926 - October 23, 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://obits.dignitymemorial.com/dignity-memorial/obituary-print.aspx?n=Barouh-Berkovits&lc=7323&pid=160615156&mid=5281962 |title=Barouh Berkovits Obituary: View Obituary for Barouh Berkovits by Levine Chapels, Brookline, MA |publisher=Obits.dignitymemorial.com |date=1926-05-07 |accessdate=2012-10-26}}</ref>) was one of the pioneers of bio-engineering, particularly the cardiac [[defibrillator]] and artificial [[cardiac pacemaker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://author.hrsonline.org/News/ep-history/notable-figures/barouhberkovits.cfm |title=Biography of Barouh V. Berkovits |publisher=Author.hrsonline.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-26}}</ref> In particular, Berkovits invented the 'demand pacemaker' and the DC defibrillator. <ref>{{cite book|title=Machines in Our Hearts: The Cardiac Pacemaker, the Implantable Defibrillator, and American Health Care|author=Kirk Jeffrey |publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press |date=2001}}</ref>
Berkovits was born in [[Czechoslovakia]]. His parents and sister perished at [[Auschwitz]]. He immigrated to the United States in the 50's, and worked for the pacemaker company [[Medtronic]] from 1975 until his retirement. In 1982, Berkovits received the 'Distinguished Scientist Award' from the Heart Rhythm Society.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Barouh V. Berkovits, MSEE (1926-2012)|author=Levy S, Medina-Ravell VA, Castellanos A|journal=Heart Rhythm|volume=10|issue=3|page=411|date=2013}}</ref>
